FBIS4-2822 "drchi072_e_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-072 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 Southeast Asia & Pacific New Envoy Wang Nongsheng Meets Leader of Western Samoa New Envoy Wang Nongsheng Meets Leader of Western Samoa OW1404041694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0409 GMT 14 Apr 94 OW1404041694 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Wellington, April 14 (XINHUA) -- Western Samoa said it is grateful to China for its assistance and has much to learn from China in the economic, social and cultural areas, said a report from Apia received here today. This was stated by Western Samoa's head of state Tanumafili II Malietoa when receiving credentials from new Chinese Ambassador Wang Nongsheng on Wednesday [13 April]. The head of state noted that Western Samoa and China have been enjoying very friendly relations since they established diplomatic relations 18 years ago. Although China is not well-off at the moment, it has extended huge and effective assistance to Western Samoa, he said. Wang Nongsheng arrived in Apia on April 10.
